A 32-year-old man was left critically injured on Saturday morning after his bikeÂ rear-ended a car on Jean Avenue in Lyttelton. "ER24 paramedics, along with other services, arrived on the scene to find a man lying next to his motorbike in the middle of the road. Medics assessed the man and found that he had sustained several injuries and was in a critical condition," spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement on Saturday. The man was subsequently treated on the scene and transported to hospital for further medical care. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.